        <body>
            <div>
                <entry xml:id="L6e59df67af524323a15864ae178a5765" n="12298">
                    <form>
                        <foreign xml:lang="gez">ንሂጒ</foreign>
                    </form>
                    <sense xml:lang="en" source="#traces" xml:id="Tmain"> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez">
                            <quote> nəhigw </quote>
                        </cit> <gramGrp>
                            <pos expand="Substantivum">subst.</pos>
                        </gramGrp> (plant) ʻForma mancante in Dillmann, che registra «nug» {<lbl expand="videas">vid.</lbl> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኑግ፡</foreign>}, <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Dillmann1865Lexicon"/>
                            <citedRange unit="c."> 675</citedRange>
                        </bibl>, come corrispondente amarico del geʻez «malans» (<bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Guidi1901Vocabolario"/>
                            <citedRange unit="c."> 397</citedRange>
                        </bibl>; <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Kane1990DictAmhVol1"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 1059</citedRange>
                        </bibl>); registrato da <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Leslau1987dic"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 394b</citedRange>
                        </bibl>; cf. tigrino «niguh», <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:DaBassano1918DictTgr"/>
                            <citedRange unit="c."> 439</citedRange>
                        </bibl> e tigrè «nehig», <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:LittmannHofner1962Tigre"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 323</citedRange>
                        </bibl>. Sulla nigella («Guizotia oleifera sive abyssinica», specie di leguminosa comestibile) vd. <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Strelcyn1973Medecine"/>
                        </bibl> sub voce: «nug».ʼ <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Lusini1996AbsadiII"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 21 n. 15</citedRange>
                        </bibl> <sense n="L" xml:id="TL"> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez">
                                <quote> nəḥigw </quote>
                            </cit> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ንሒጕ</foreign>( <bibl>
                                <ptr target="bm:Dasta1969AmhDict"/>
                                <citedRange unit="page"> 837</citedRange>
                            </bibl>), <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez">
                                <quote> nəhigw </quote>
                            </cit> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ንሂጕ</foreign> (Lt) ‘leguminous plant that has oily seeds’; ʻ(<cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez">
                                <quote> qəbʿa nəḥigw </quote>
                            </cit> oil made from the nəḥigw-plant‘; is used for cooking, especially during the fasting period) <bibl>
                                <ptr target="bm:Leslau1987dic"/>
                                <citedRange unit="page"> 394b</citedRange>
                            </bibl> </sense> <nd/> </sense>
                </entry>
